name: Mr Inbetween
overview: Ray Shoesmith is a father, ex-husband, boyfriend and best friend: tough roles to juggle in the modern age. Even harder when you’re a criminal for hire.

episodes.name: The Pee Pee Guy
episodes.overview: A business associate falls from grace, while Ray takes the fall for a mate. A chance meeting in the park and a new apprentice.

episodes.name: Unicorns Know Everybody's Name
episodes.overview: The wrong guy gets the good news and Unicorns do exist. The first of a thousand kisses and good ole revenge.

episodes.name: Captain Obvious
episodes.overview: Anger mismanagement and no such thing as Jesus. If you can’t kill your own brother-in-law, who can?

episodes.name: On Behalf Of Society
episodes.overview: Ray doesn’t like surprises, sit downs, sandwiches, or assholes. Brittany asks tough questions, while Ray hands out trouble to those that seek it.

episodes.name: Hard Worker
episodes.overview: People are not always what they appear to be and a good strong name is important. It’s also important to lock your car when you leave it.

episodes.name: Your Mum's Got a Strongbox
episodes.overview: A nutritious breakfast is the key to good health, as is looking in the trunk before stealing a car; people say they like surprises, but that is debatable.

episodes.name: Shoulda Tapped
episodes.overview: Ray don’t tap but he gives good advice. Sometimes you have to take the scenic route.

episodes.name: Don't Be a Dickhead
episodes.overview: Ray solves problems but under no circumstances does he answer questions.

episodes.name: I Came from Your Balls?
episodes.overview: Ray and Ally get caught out and good dental hygiene is as important as paying your debts.

episodes.name: Monsters
episodes.overview: Is there really any such thing as monsters?

episodes.name: Can't Save You
episodes.overview: All things must end, even Christmas.

episodes.name: Let Me Stop You There
episodes.overview: Lady troubles, old friends and hearts on trees.

episodes.name: Watch Out for Snakes
episodes.overview: Ray does favors but doesn't forgive.

episodes.name: See You in Your Dreams
episodes.overview: An old friend takes the fall and an associate pays for past misdeeds.

episodes.name: Socks Are Important
episodes.overview: When exiting a department store, make sure you don’t leave with less than you came with.

episodes.name: Nice Face
episodes.overview: Enemies may come and go, as do friends.

episodes.name: There Rust, and Let Me Die
episodes.overview: One lives, but it is unknown if anybody really dies.

episodes.name: Coulda Shoulda
episodes.overview: If your mistakes lead to your death, how can you learn from them?

episodes.name: Champ
episodes.overview: If you think violence is not the answer, you don’t understand the question.

episodes.name: All I Ever Wanted
episodes.overview: You can't make anybody stay but you can sure as hell make ‘em go.

episodes.name: Cut the Crap Princess
episodes.overview: Curiosity rarely kills the cat but too many pharmaceuticals generally will.

episodes.name: Before I Went to War
episodes.overview: All is fair in love and war but not in business. Forgiveness may be divine but revenge is way more fun.

episodes.name: Ray Who?
episodes.overview: Don't live in the past they say but what if it's a hell of a lot better than the present?

episodes.name: I'm Your Girl
episodes.overview: Everybody loves a road trip.

episodes.name: I'll See You Soon
episodes.overview: There's a reason why the road less travelled is less travelled.

episodes.name: I'm Not Leaving
episodes.overview: If nothing ends, what begins?
